# Implementation Plan - Agent Architecture Refactor

# Goal Description
Refactor the backend to support a modular, plugin-based Agent architecture. This allows new agents to be added by simply creating a new folder/file, which the Maestro agent will automatically discover and utilize ("Flexible Playlist").

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This refactor changes the `backend/` structure significantly.
> [backend/agent.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/backend/agent.py) will be deprecated in favor of `backend/agents/` directory.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Refactor
#### [NEW] [backend/agents/base.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/backend/agents/base.py)
- Abstract Base Class `Agent`.
- Attributes: `name`, `description`, `slug`.
- Methods: `async def execute(self, context: dict) -> dict`.

#### [NEW] [backend/agents/registry.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/backend/agents/registry.py)
- `AgentRegistry` class.
- Scans `backend/agents/` for subclasses of `Agent`.
- Provides `get_all_agents()` and `get_agent(slug)`.

#### [NEW] [backend/agents/maestro/agent.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/backend/agents/maestro/agent.py)
- Moves logic from [agent.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/backend/agent.py).
- Updates system prompt to dynamically include descriptions of ALL other agents found in the Registry.
- This enables the "Flexible Playlist" - Maestro sees what tools are available at runtime.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/main.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/backend/main.py)
- Initialize `AgentRegistry` on startup.
- Update `/agent/generate` to use the refactored Maestro.

### Developer Experience
#### [NEW] [run_all.bat](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/run_all.bat)
- One-click script to start Neo4j (check), Backend, and Frontend.

#### [NEW] [AGENT_DEV_GUIDE.md](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver1/AGENT_DEV_GUIDE.md)
- Documentation on implementing the `Agent` class and registering it.

